The master Luciano glacier Ferrari explained firstly to participants the ideal characteristics of ice.
Is crucial not only the right flavor, but also the flexibility soyeuse and the right consistency.
However, Luciano does not forget during the training the icing on the cake of the national superstructure and, in general, southern Italian: "The ice is simply the best: and she retains a dose of romanticism."
The first step in the production seems simple.
Luciano pays the basic ingredients, such as milk, cream, milk powder, sugar and stabilisers in a large mélangeur said all 85 degrees through an electronic programme and cooling immediately to four degrees.
He then opened a tap installed on the machine: it has a basic white cream pasteurized milk, the foundation of all kinds of ice.
The trainer is also beset by question: Is it possible to make ice using only natural substances without stabilising?
How can we give free rein to the personal pleasure of experimentation?
Mr Luciano warns against the fact be misled by the spirit of the time.
Anyone who does that ice "made from natural ingredients," has perhaps despite this used stabilisers: the more often a natural product, for example, of the seed meal of guar achieved from the guar bean.
It is of course possible to manufacture of stabilising the ice without using, just to sell within 24 hours, otherwise it collapses and the client croquera nothing other than ice pellet.
Some of the basic mass modifications are permitted.
This becomes more exciting with flavourings.
The master Luciano establishes the difference between the ingredients that one gains in the fruit or sweets of the supermarket.
In addition, there are the powder and pulp.
"suppliers will try all of you pass dozens of aromatised ingredients."
"however, you should simply try."
In the revenues of sorbets fruit with sugar and fresh fruit.
In the icy creams made from the mass of white, adding eggs becomes a yellow cream and, when combined with cocoa powder, the basis of all the possible chocolate desserts.
Now, all participants in the use of ice machines.
Luciano invited from time to time to produce four types of ice: vanilla, chocolate, the moka and hazelnuts, with or without eggs, with varying degrees of vanilla aroma or other natural ingredients.
The different kinds of ice to the fruit are also subject to the same experience.
More aromatic substances, more fruit purée: from the point of view of the taste, that is not necessarily better.
The ice is not necessarily the taste of the nuts, hazelnuts when it consists largely of hazelnuts.
The ice in the kiwi fruit, very popular, is made from the group using more fruit, less water and a little less of stabilizing.
"only a balanced mix is the taste of ice," says Luciano correctly.
The manufacture of ice is an exercise of calculation: if the use of fishing puree with a lot of sugar, the amount of sugar must be reduced in the basic recipe.
A sugar supplement is necessary for the ice in lemon.
Luciano has a device with which it determines the sugar content of different types of fruit (the wine growers are used to measure the degree of Oechsle in the grape must).
Fortunately, the tables are extending the calculations.
The manufacture of ice does not require, as in the past, physical intervention.
This is not only the mass of manufacturing the machine autocategorizers basis that helps.
There is also a device which is simultaneously the mixture of ice available to make it onctueux and reduced to low temperatures.
In spite of all the automatisations, small failures are not excluded.
The Brazilian Gustavo barbouille of fruit puree from head to feet and, thus, éclabousse his comrades when the control of huge bowl mélangeur escapes.
The master Luciano is of the opinion that a "incident is likely to occur in each course: it is only a matter of time."
