An opinion indicates that exploits all reliable data, including those of the industry as long as they are of good quality work.
It does not prohibit experts working for the EU--have Efsa to establish contact with this sector of activity.
But they should make them public.
Mr Kuiper admits that it works for the International Institute for the life sciences (International Life Sciences Institute, Ilsi) based in the United States.
The organization sees itself as a neutral forum bringing together which, among other things, belong to the field of science, industry and the policy in order to assess the risks of biotechnology without being in the pay of a lobby.
In this case, the independent experts such as Mr's subsequent work resent the fact that genetically modified crops will be accepted without any food testing in animals and Pe9233.htm not tested the impact of these plants on the environment.
"we want to know what is, for example, the impact of genetically modified maize field," says Mr subsequent work.
