A mosque to Temecula received the unanimous support of the local planning committee after more than five hours of public testimony, often heated.
Critics attacked the project, arguing that it was the promotion of terrorism as well as traffic congestion.
But Commissioners have ruled on Wednesday evening that the new religious centre comply with local laws and that it would be esthétiquement impressive.
