The lion is ready to be ashamed of, the restructuring of GMMs is awaiting the final green light of the court
After 18 months of turmoil and uncertainty, GMMs has finally been given the green light to start from scratch.
A federal bankruptcy judge in New York, was officially praised Thursday the "pre-packaged" by creditors plan that approximately $5 billion of the debt would be deleted, opening the way to the business of entertainment, with 86 years of existence, to focus its efforts on the production and distribution of films and television programs.
With Thursday's decision, that the plan meets the requirements of the code of the bankruptcy of the United States, there are still no legal obstacle to GMMs to stay afloat under the tutelage of the founders of entertainment Spyglass, Gary Barber and Roger Birnbaum, who will become the directors-general of what will be a studio.
Staff will be reduced to about 320 in 400.
GMMs will not emerge from Chapter 11 as; Chase will not have a credit facility of $500 million, to finance the new operations and products of GMMs.
It is being distributed under licence by the investment bank, which is itself at $75 million, and should be funded to mid-December.
The process of restructuring of the studio began in May 2009 when the investment bank Moelis & Co. was committed to advise the direction on how to get its finances as it did not have the means to pay the interest amounting to $300 million per year.
In August, the director general, Harry Sloan, has been replaced by Stephen Cooper, a former CEO of Enron and an expert in recovery known for his work in Krispy Kreme Doughnuts.
The attempts of Moelis and Cooper to resolve the financial difficulties of conducting research and the more than 140 creditors of the studio have taken much longer than expected.
After several months of discussions, the parties have agreed, at the end of 2009, put the company up for sale.
However, the auction attracted little of bidders including none of them was prepared to pay the $2 billion more in which creditors were to research.
In the spring of this year, it was again while the GMMs team had started working on a restructuring plan which, after months of disagreements and internal debates, has finally been approved by the creditors at the end of October.
When GMMs officially fate of bankruptcy in the following weeks, businesses Moelis and Cooper bonuses of millions of dollars for their work.
Moelis & Co., which has already received $1.2 million, will receive a payment of $9.5 million.
Cooper, companies that have collected $375 000 per month for their services to .corporate management, will receive a "success fee" of $4 million.
Barber and Birnbaum account to boost production of GMMs, which has released only one movie this year, and set up an annual list of seven or eight films from 2012.
They also intend to co-finance two films based on "the Hobbit," with Warner Bros
The studio must conclude a separate loan between $265 000 000 and $275 million to fund its share in these two films, which must be achieved by Peter Jackson.
The investor Carl Icahn, which holds about 18% of the debt of GMMs, tried to achieve a merger of the studio with Lions Gate entertainment, where it is the main shareholder.
However, the recent discussions between the two companies have not led to an agreement.
I think toys to maintain your gifts budget in balance
Although the main candidate for this year is the most wonderful toy, perhaps, the IPAD, followed by the video game system of Microsoft, Kinect, both can make a significant gap in your budget gifts.
Consider that, for the price of an iPad, you can buy five bicycles BMX $99 and a game Kinect cost the same amount as 10 strings to classical jump of pearls, or approximately 48 boxes of Play-Doh.
But there are ways to keep your gifts budget in balance.
Recently, I visited three national sellers of toys - Wal-Mart, Toys "R" Us and Wholesale Club BJ - to see electronic toys that I could buy for less than $80.
It is clear that the --Moore Law has evolved, the technological toy of this year is likely to have more strength; while costing the same price, if not a little less, compared to last year.
In addition, there is generally less than new toys associated with Web sites, two of the best known of this type, Webkinz and Penguin Club, have more tender.
And toys to button batteries are increasing, as well as toys to rechargeable batteries.
A few recommendations.
(all prices are from Toys "R" Us, unless otherwise indicated.)
The Sing-a-ma-jigs (Mattel, $13 for 3 years and older) are toys of the size of a guinea pig who sing a note when you press them down.
Pressure is equal to a note, and a second call a song.
If you buy several, they sing in harmony.
