Siemens Red Bull triumph in F1 with a secret weapon
A software creates improvements on cars in real time.
As soon as Red Bull tructurally entered the world of Formula 1 in 2004, its history in this sélecte universe of the speed was marked by the surprise and the success.
In a first time, nobody has taken account of the options for a new stable that were to happen, despite the upward trajectory of recent seasons, the last November, in the last phase of the championship all have counted on the triumph of Fernando Alonso's Ferrari.
Without discounting the champion's skill as a pilot, the German Sebastien Vette, the ability of the Renault engine which drives his car, in the world of Formula 1 refers to the legend of the "secret weapon" that the multinational company Siemens has put in the hands of Red Bull to turn in a winning team.
It is in fact a powerful simulation software to process that the German company has launched on the market in 2007 with very distant goals of the High automobilistique competition.
Appointed PLM, electronic-data-processing-related powerful instrument has been used to create chains assembly factories fabricantes of everyone, of energy stations, of high precision instruments.
The objective is faithfully reproduce, simulate the product or process before the building of a real way, thus avoiding the defects and avoidable costs.
Plm facilitated the development of Canon cameras, Sukhoi aircraft or of Nissan's most famous vehicles.
Siegfried Russwurm, responsible for the industrial division of Siemens, explains the fact that the use of this instrument technology in its plant in Formula 1 Red Bull to create and execute "in the coming hours, almost in real time," changes, changes and improvements detected during races and tests.
Russwurm explains that the Augean 1992 had an average of 10 technicians in their teams that was able to introduce a maximum of three or four improvements on vehicles each season.
In the Red Bull team today are 180 young professionals of high qualifications, equipped with powerful computer equipment are tall, any kind of changes on the speed-enthused.
The leader of Siemens explained that the software PLM is able to analyse and improve all the elements of speed-enthused Red Bull except the engine, which is the exclusive responsibility of Renault.
We change the materials, the fuel, aerodynamics and security features.
The changes may pass from the virtual reality simulator to the reality in less than 24 hours, thanks to advanced systems of production by laser and autoclaves.
As single limitation of this madness of technological development there is the amount of $40 million that each team of Formula 1 may spend as limit each season to facilitate competition.
Red Bull has established the factory of high technology to create and speed-enthused in a town 50 miles from London.
These are two buildings where the visits, especially for journalists, are limited.
Everything that is happening there is considered "top secret."
The staff for this duty has 580 people, ci-inclus two pilots, the champion Vettel and Mark Webber.
The hero of the Formula 1 of Red Bull, without doubt, is the recent champion Sebastian Vetell.
Between the technological resources that the mark of energy drinks has the benefit of its participation in the circuits, there are other hidden protagonists, whose activity is invaluable and the fame no.
The director of technology of the factory, Steve Nevey, says that five years ago you could say that the progress of R + D in the case of racing cars were making the 50% of victories and the pilots were responsible for the rest.
Today these percentages have changed and the technology represents the 85% of success, while the pilots provide 15% of the value added.
Nevey admit that the Vettel or Webber will never be replaced by the computer, because "they are unpredictable gladiators."
HP come in two 20 s own shops with local distributors
Hewlett-Packard (HP) has opened its first store in Barcelona exclusive in collaboration with his partner Pont Reyes.
This will be the first of the network of 20 businesses between 80 and 100 square metres that the multinational plans to install in Spain during the next two years.
The company will this initiative with the 16 areas that are already in multi-brand sales centres such as PC City, Carrefour, Saturn and El Corte store.
The Vice-President of HP Spain, Helena Herrero, gave as an example the revised store located on the Gran Vía Barcelona, property of Pont Reyes, with which it 30 years that it works.
The North American group has prepared a plan to bring 200 points of sale in Europe in 2013, which includes the Spanish 20 establishments.
The first open were those of Bucharest (Romania) and Belgrade (Serbia) last week, the Barcelona Process is the third.
Herrero did not want to reveal the possible next stores, even if it has confessed that Madrid could be the next destination.
The head of personal HMS systems has ensured that the philosophy for the location of stores will always be the same, with the support of a local distributor with experience and knowledge of the sector.
The North American group advise and exclusive deals with the design of the furniture stores (with products that can be affected in an interactive way), which held an identical image in Europe.
In addition, HP covers staff training establishments.
Helena Herrero has denied that it is a system of frankness and pointed out that the exclusive network of shops claims to "improve the service to clients and SMEs in the purchase, the assistance, the post-vente and even the packaging."
The store of Barcelona includes a pioneering space with a pilot programme to global level that solves the possible problems of HP computer equipment.
An online service connects with a technical centre in Maastricht (Netherlands).
"thus, in 10 minutes we can solve problems that can often take two days."
"this system is designed specifically for the MPEs and users, because the big companies have already contracted services of technical assistance," remarked yesterday Helena Herrero.
