More optimistic than other leaders, the deputy head delegate of Banco Sabadell, Jaime Guardiola, believe that 2011 will be a hard year for the banking sector, but initially rejected a new liquidity crisis and predicted the end of the war liabilities.
Despite this, it provides a collapse of interest margins, that we will try to offset some with incréments of committees and the price of credit.
Sabadell look capture in three years a million retail customers, its task.
Sabadell has found a way to exploit during the future three years and to be able to survive in a very difficult economic environment.
The bank will set in motion in 2011 a new management plan which will hold a will labilité of three years.
The objective, in part to survive without the need for public subsidies of FROB, is to win a rating of market by harnessing a million new retail customers - 700,000 if you deducted those who are able to get out of the banque-, its great task, because until now the bank had ruined more SMEs and that the particular client companies.
This year it has collected 250,000 retail customers and 50,000 companies.
His ratings of individuals market is 3.5%, while the companies it exceeds the 10%.
Another 2011-2013 plan is the gamble on productivity, or what is the same thing, austerity, with the reduction of costs as objective, the provocations of which will be explained by the bank when it presents the results of the exercise.
Few other banks now dare to set targets and the public do, because the financial crisis has caused concern among all the plans of the global banking sector.
Sabadell, in fact, will finalise its master plan this year Optima, sets out four years ago, although initially the plan was for three years, but the market situation has determined the extension for a year.
The clients who escape the coffers of savings will be its main objective.
During a breakfast organized by FIPA, Guardiola has insisted on the fact that 2011 will be a difficult year "and overwhelming."
The executive, in fact, think that the exit from the crisis in Spain "will be slow."
In addition, two or three years it will be "very difficult to create jobs," which is fundamental to the survival of the banking business, has insisté-t-il.
And even if he thinks that the war liabilities - which penalises the margins - is reduced, the price of risk premiums that banks and building societies pay for its emissions for liquidity are already moving to the price of credit to compensate for the fall in margins.
"the aspect of the liquidity and funding is structural and will be a factor of pressure on the credit."
"we do not have tightened the tap, but the differentials are higher," acknowledged Guardiola.
BANESTO has already given orders to its network of limiting the long-term credit and increase the price differentials - see 22 and 27 November- CincoDías.
He also admitted that the trend of the banking sector now "is to increase the committees," but "there is a competitive framework."
The master plan of Sabadell is based on organic growth even if, as always, the group does not eliminate the possibility of corporate operations.
This is not in vain that it ensures that Spain "will be asked of larger dimensions."
"next year," assuré-t-il move.
He says that the needs of capital "leadership role" and some Spanish financial entity could enter the red numbers.
And he noted that the FROB can replace the market in the diversion of funds in the case of new recapitalization.
After having assured that Sabadell can survive in the temporal closure of the markets, it has diminished the importance of the fact that some predict a new banking crisis of liquidity.
But on the contrary of what happened in June, GIHR cannot provide the short-term funding can be obtained through rest, which dampens the crisis.
