Zapatero and the German red line
Berlin has opted to remain in the euro, but he established the conditions for the entire Union.
Market tensions have led to a llama doble government response.
On the one hand, José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero announced new methods of adjustment, which vary from tax reductions for SMEs, regulation of private placement agencies or removal of EUR 426 in aid for the unemployed without professional contribution to the privatisation of the 49% of AENA, Barajas airport management and El Prat and 30% of the State Loteries.
On the other, the Vice-President Elena Salgado, with the support of the former President Felipe González, with Chancellor Angela Merkel's criticism in regard to its responsibility to post the current crisis.
How are these movements?
It should be noted that the position of Merkel is not a mistake in its forthcoming policy.
On the contrary, it is another limitation of the difficult process of redefinition of the euro.
And Germany has a radically new vision of what should be its future, which shocked with that to maintain the old traditions of most of its partners.
Faced with European resistance, in Germany we are starting to speculate on the three possible ways out of the crisis.
The first, a strong euro, integrated by itself, Austria and the Netherlands, among other countries, and the south would abandon the monetary zone.
The second, the recovery of Mark, even if it seems of science fiction, with a very favourable tide of opinion, nearly a 50% of the population.
The third, a new design of the euro, in line with the German proposals for a greater macroeconomic control, budgetary rigour, fines on countries that break, of a possible suspension of payments and extension to the private sector of the costs of potential adjustments.
The German position is clear and it's been a long time that it is now, therefore there is no place for excuses.
First, in 2009, when both IMF as the European Commission stimulated deficits, the German Government has invented a constitutional reform to prevent them from 2016.
This was the first signal of difference between what Germany felt that we needed to do (fiscal austerity plans and stability of public finances) and its European partners, ci-inclut France, practised.
The second Central European countries was when Merkel has hardly extended the decision to save Greece.
From then on it was the subject of fierce criticism, but the truth is that the political consensus in Germany and public opinion and the published were against the rescue of Greece.
Finally, towards the end of October, Merkel expresses a clear position again, in calling for the reform of the Treaties of the Union to make possible the rescue of a country and force at the same time to private lenders to contribute to the cost.
This position has been interpreted as anti-European, because it has left the Irish crisis and the rest.
But its proposal, although watered down a little, has been approved and, the following month, we should see the process of reform of the Union that these measures from 2013.
Germany has outlined a red line that it does not think cross.
And she tells us that, even if we must take measures with which it is not too agree, as of that date, the former functioning of the euro would have ended.
2013 will see the birth of a new monetary zone, in which the countries which contravene the rules will be severely punished, they may be forced to be declared in default and, in this case, the private sector will also be a party of the costs.
Germany tells us that we must follow a strict growth with high rates of savings and investment, moderation in consumption, improvements in productivity and competitiveness and positive external balances.
An alternative based on debt and the construction, with huge holes in the balance of payments, such as the one who chaired the Spanish growth in the years of the boom, will simply not be tolerated.
The development is clear.
And it would be wrong not to hear.
It is not only to renew the public deficit to 3% in 2013.
What we are being asked for is much harder.
And what they must not do in these circumstances is to deceive ourselves.
I hope that the current turbulence happen to us a greater tranquillity.
And that we can seize the opportunity that we were given, in the spring of 2013.
It seems that President Zapatero has also heard of this form and its dual statement (the reforms promised after the meeting of the past Saturday with large companies and yesterday's announcement of new measures) suggests that, despite the criticism of Merkel, it opened the way to the theory that park.visitation.continues.to.decline, .probably.due.to.a. agenda at home.
But the red line that Germany has mapped out is, and they do not seem to move.
And among the possibilities that, we cannot exclude that to abandon a monetary zone too chock-full of countries seriously.
And in this case, Germany we can always say that she had warned.
Sport and fraud of the law
The tricks similar to that of Alonso and Ramos against Ajax show the ingenuity but not the desire to escape punishment.
The expulsion conversation in principle by two players of Real Madrid (Xabi Alonso and Sergio Ramos) during the 23 November match against Ajax in the Champions League has caused rivers of ink on the anti-sportif nature of such behaviour and if both players should be punished by UEFA.
As we know, a few minutes before completing the match (clearly that their team already earned), the two players have deliberately lost the time when they have made mistakes in determining the referee to show them the second yellow card.
As well, and given that Real Madrid will eventually be leader of his group, the two players, will take the XVIII. regulatory dam during the next game of the match against Auxerre and can go ahead without cartons to the next phase.
Finally, the discipline committee of UEFA has punished with two matches the coach of the team, Mourinho and different economic are the players involved.
The provocation of a yellow card in www.eumc.eu.int or similar circumstances is not a new practice, www.oag-bvg.gc.ca rather common in the world of football.
It is so widespread that it is part of the ethos, Asia, but of the sport.
Part of the debate emerged in the case say is due to the fact that this has had as a team of the entity of Real Madrid (which in its anthem nobility and the honour and which in the past Opportunitites players were fined for similar acts) and the orchestrated dramatization, it appears, by Mourinho, which adds one more episode to its inflated history of technician histrionique and provocative.
In any case, the debate whether this type of behaviour not expressly prohibited by the regulation contradicts the principles of sport, i.e., if with these actions committing a fraud of law; because, in fact, they are friendly actions with the sporting regulation, but seem to avoid.
The question is to look at the type of damage they cause to the sporting spirit.
One of the goods which includes the sporting spirit is the physical integrity of opposing players, an aspect that, with these actions has not been put in danger, there was no violent game.
Another of these goods that we talk with the proper game is that the team of players infracteurs unfairly take advantage of the opposite team, which is not the case.
The paradoxical fact of Real Madrid players, however, is that it does not accept that is normally characterised as cheating o fraud of the law, because its violation of rules has not been conducted behind closed doors to try to avoid the penalty, but their action has tried to be as clear as possible to receive the penalisation of the referee.
They expected and they have gladly accepted the sanction.
Another question is the kind of advantage that the infracteurs receive the mistakes people.
Here it seems necessary that we do not put at a disadvantage to rival and has an advantage in the same match, because obviously the result of the action from their own team with fewer players.
And this is not an useful strategy for the next game, because the club could not count on these players.
Obviously the advantage lies in the fact that the players will start the next phase of the Champions League without cards that can threaten their future participation in a match.
But it is a long-term benefit, with a degree of ambiguity, because the team could be eliminated all of a sudden and, with this action players perform a match of XVIII. and spend the second round of boxes, in which the suspension due to the accumulation of cards is with a less than in the first round.
So that, climb to the top, this is not so clear that this is an advantage.
Ultimately, these actions are not contrary to the spirit of sport, which is still part of strategic decisions that promote the maximum advantage of what the rules allow.
In our case, the players have not set up to avoid the application of the penalty (it would be a clear case of fraud), otherwise they chose the moment in which they are subject to it.
They have made a strategic decision without disrupting the penalty or flee.
Even if the border between the engineering and fraud of the law is A-GG-, in this opportunity I think that there has been a clear case of genius.
The controversy, it seems to me, is due to two factors: because there were two auto-expulsions and because of the way of conveying the Executive Director for the cause.
The damage caused to the principles of ethical sport by these actions is not as much as aesthetic.
