China maintains the objectives of reducing greenhouse gases
The representative of the country in the COP16 assured that his country has made strenuous efforts to reduce the trace of coal and detailed that it maintains its offer to reduce up to 2020 between 40 and 45 percent of greenhouse gas emissions.
China keeps its offer to cut between 40 and 45 percent of greenhouse gas emissions before 2020, Su Wei, representative of this country to the COP16.
In his first public appearance in the 16 th Conference of the Parties of the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change (COP16), Su Wei has assured that his country has made enormous efforts to reduce the trace of coal and convert its industry.
In fact, has exposé-t-il, the last four years the country has inverti $245 million in the efforts to reduce the emission of greenhouse gases.
However, it has clearly stated that China will not change its objectives, but it will continue to work together with the international community in this area.
He mentioned that the Chinese strategy in the field of climate change is divided into four areas: dialogue; capacity building; construction of institutions and support for pilot programs.
There has been progress in all these areas, ci-inclut approval, last year, a new Energy Act, which recognises the objectives addressed in regard to the reduction of greenhouse gases, has expliqué-t-il.
On the other hand, he pointed out that in China, the federal authorities have been working in a coordinated way with the local government and to achieve the objectives of energy saving, energy efficient use and reduction of emissions.
In addition, has déclaré-t-il, there are various multiannual plans underway or completed, both funded by the Chinese government as by the governments of other countries.
For example, has mentionné-t-il, the Program of Energy Use Efficiente, which was implémenté during the last five years and has received investment from the United Nations (UN), the government and the private initiative.
There is also a provincial project of climate change, another for the change of light bulbs with energy-saving lamps and another mitigation and adaptation, has détaillé-t-il.
At the same table, Martin Krol, scientific adviser to the government of this country as regards climate change, has ensured that the efforts of China have been greatest of what we think.
For example, has exposé-t-il, per capita emissions of greenhouse gases in China is three tonnes per person, while in the United States it is 100 tonnes; China is responsible for 9% of the historic contribution in the contamination.
Likewise, it has made unprecedented efforts in the use of energy, how to increase a 20% energy efficiency in the last five years and plans to make another similar to 2020, has déclaré-t-il.
