With the duel of Santos Laguna and Monterrey in the final, in addition, there are two different styles themselves, marked by their technicians, who find them a sharp contrast with the results.
Rubén Omar Romano has had three defeats in the final, it has had ups and downs in his career, but he has been able to achieve three times the decisive series, although so far it has not hit the mark and that is why this is a very special occasion for him.
The Argentine has to be content with the coin of sous-champion, he remained a step behind the winners and curiously consecutive final with the same team he has played.
The strategist santiste arrived at its first final as entraineur in the Tournoi Call 2002, when he took the reins of Morelia with which he has lost with an overall score of 4-2 against Toluca; later, in the 2003 Closing it happened at the decisive duel and lost again with the overall outcome of 3-1 and this was precisely against Rayados.
With Santos Laguna already, in the Tournoi Bicentenaire 2010, against the Diablos, Rubén has suffered a setback, because his team has done an equal match of 2-2 against the Choriceros after 210 minutes of the game, but in the series of penalties he received an advantage for 3-1 with two opportunities to finally get the title and three of his players have missed 11 metres and he has suffered the leap of 4-3.
Rubén has lost two final with the Diablos Rojos and with Monterrey, his rival in the tournament, therefore it does not have the same fate, he tries to let go of the curse to be able to celebrate a title for the first time, although it says that the institution is more important for him.
"I want to be champion, I do not want to break no statistics, this is for a club, not for a passion, and therefore I will obtain the title, but what I mentioned before is more important," commented the helmsman when he was asked what would be its weak points in the final.
He remembers a lot of the final last, of which it ensures that he has learned a lot, "the only lesson we can learn is that until the referee blows the final, we cannot celebrate, we are prepared in line, the players too, because the last time, with two penalties to draw we were already prepared to run and I believe that this is a lesson, before the end of the match cannot celebrate."
He knows that this series could be defined by penalties, which does not worry, because it says in its players: "We never seeks to arrive at the series of penalties, we try to finish in the regular time, but sometimes we have that we prepare, the previous tournament we have been prepared, unfortunately the fate we sometimes made a wrong turn, these are the emotions or the anguish to take the title in our hands, hands we escaped, it served as a lesson for us this final and we hope that there is more in this position."
Romano now has the opportunity to be a technician sous-champion and for the first time the glory of the securities.
The European Union is changing the rules for the visa
The people must go to WCPU centres for Visa Demandeurs before their interview in Section Consulaire; the costly waiting time will be smaller.
From 10 January 2011 the processing of visas to the Embassy and consulates in the United States will change.
With the new procedure, the majority of applicants will have to stand for WCPU centres for the Demandeurs of Visa (CSA, according to its symbols) before their interview in the Consulaire Section.
The CSA staff will take biometric information, which will be reviewed by the Section Consulaire before the interview.
The new procedure will present some benefits for candidates, including mentions the following:
The total cost to deal with the visa will be lower, it will no longer be necessary to make a payment to get an appointment, another payment for the treatment of the visa and another for the courier service delivers the document.
The aspiring will make an one-time payment which will cover the three services.
The current tariff will remain the same: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 in the case of visas with request (ci-inclut visas for temporary workers) and $390 for visas for traders and investors.
The people who want to renew their visas will not have to go to an interview with the Consulaire Representative, they only come to the CSA closer where they will present the documents and will take their fingerprints.
Because biometric information will be made in the CSA, applicants who want a second event to be interviewed in the Section Consulaire stay there less time than before.
Similarly, the visa applicants to Consulats of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer pay the extra fee of $26.
For other information on the new procedure to apply for the visa, visit the following page http: / / mexico.usembassy.gov / boletines / sp101201 _ Visas-FAQs.html
NASA will announce the discovery of extraterrestrial life
The space agency of the United States has cited the press to be presenting a discovery that will have the impact on the research of living in space.
The National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) of the United States will tomorrow, Thursday, a discovery astrobiologique, which could prove the theory of the existence of extraterrestrial life.
The discovery will be presented in a press conference on Thursday at 13: 00 p.m. at NASA headquarters in Washington for astrobiology, science experts who studied the origin, development, distribution and future of life in the universe.
When she pointed to the press, NASA has assured that it will issue that will have the impact on the search for extraterrestrial life ', which has raised speculation of the experts from other countries.
The discovery could prove the theory that there are similar to creatures and hostile to us that it was uninhabited and would put on the table the possibility of becoming intelligent beings as humans if its living conditions are improved.
It appears that there is talk of a microbe discovered at the bottom of Mono Lake in the National Park Yosemite, California, who lives in an ambient that it was too poisonous for any form of life, because the lake is rich in arsénique.
In any form, the creature uses the arsénique as a way of life and that leads us to believe that a similar life could exist on other planets that have not our atmosphere.
According to the astrobiologistes, if these agencies use the arsénique in their metabolism, this proves that "there is another form of life, a second form of life, different than we are."
The space agency will contact the true scope of discoveries in the press conference tomorrow, Thursday.
The conference will be the géobiologie Pamela Conrad, who is studying the possibility of life on Mars; and the biologist Steven Benner, one of the scientists who study Titan (the largest satellite of Saturn), under the prospect of its chemistry is similar to that of the Earth.
