14 suspected drug traffickers arrested
A dozen searches were conducted in the Eastern Townships, Wednesday, in the framework of the dismantling of a network of production and sale of cannabis.
Fourteen people have been arrested and will face various charges.
The searches were conducted in Sherbrooke, Orford and Stoke, mostly in places that were used in the production of drugs.
"approximately 750 plants of cannabis, four kilos of hashish, money and equipment that were used to production have been seized," said Louis-Philippe Ruel, spokesman of the Sûreté du Quebec.
In total, eleven men and three women have been arrested, including two heads alleged leaders of this network, two men of Sherbrooke.
The people arrested were to appear at the Palace of Justice in Sherbrooke in the hours of their arrest.
They could face charges of cannabis production, possession for the purpose of trafficking, conspiracy and theft of services, among others.
These searches took place as the result of a lengthy investigation, which lasted almost a year.
"this is information received from the public which has enabled us to make these arrests," said Mr Ruel.
Some 70 police officers on Regional module in the Eastern Townships of the Sûreté du Québec, of the Police Service of Sherbrooke and the Régie de police Memphrémagog, police took part in this operation.
