The Montréal of Algerian origin Nacereddine Zemmal has a very particular journey.
The athlete who excels in "sanda" (kung-fu "full contact"), in kickboxing and Thai boxing gets on the tatamis and rings of the world in search of new challenges.
"I started to play the martial arts as the kung-fu and the kickboxing 12 years ago, in Algeria, explained Zemmal, installed in the mainland since 2008 to develop among professionals."
"in my case, I am looking for fighting everywhere, as for those who do not like the game ground-firing present mixed martial arts, the competitions are rare in North America."
Recently, anyone who has worked as a security officer and as a clerk for the company UPS has issued bad news to his rivals, winning two gold medals in the finals of the amateur world of the World Karate and Kickboxing Association (WKA), from 23 to 30 October, in Edinburgh, Scotland.
"I won the categories of kickboxing full contact and Thai boxing, he explained."
"currently, I am preparing to go to China for the World Cup of san shou."
"those who have finished in the top four at the last World Cup in each category were invited."
"I won the bronze in 2009 in Toronto."
"in 2005, in Vietnam, I have finished eighth."
"in 2007, in China, I concluded the tournament in the fifth, when I came in third in Toronto in 2009, he added."
"what is interesting is that I have made to each competition."
"at this rate, I will be first this time or next year!"
The "san shou" or "sanda" is a discipline from China where fisticuffs, and that ground-firing projections, are allowed.
The duels originally on a platform and more rarely in a ring.
The battle is the American pugiliste from this form of Vietnamese origin Cung The, well known in the world of martial arts.
If Nacer Zemmal has only one event in his career, he will certainly its presence to the "King Sanda" super tournament, the Super Bowl of kung-fu.
"this competition is the most prestigious more raised and in China, explained the sympathetic gaillard."
"this is the equivalent of the Stade Lumpinee (the biggest stage of Thailand)."
"that was a great experience."
Zemmal won his first fight, in the semi-finals of its category (80 kg), before losing the final.
"anyone who has defeated me was a true pro, he analysed."
"there are four combatants by category (80 kg, 85 kg, 90 kg and 90 kg)."
"the winners of the semi-final games are in their final category."
"then, the winners of each category face to crown a champion alone, the King of kung-fu."
450 million in contracts
OTC Hydro-Québec was awarded $450 million in contracts to firms for the Eastmain- 1 hydroelectric project -A-Sarcelle-Rupert.
At the heart of this avalanche of more than 100 contracts, it is a consortium of OPI firms, Dessau, SM Group and Axor which won the most important, the stewardship of the project, for a total of $295 million without tender.
This consortium called Energy Stewardship was established in 2004 associated with the choice of going private sector hydroelectric its responsibility to manage this important project of $5 billion.
At the beginning of 2005, the Energy Stewardship consortium to pick up the lucrative contract without competitive bidding.
For the Parti Quebecois, the use of business consortia poses a serious ethical problem that risk to eliminate competition and lead to a rise in the price.
"it is the new way of making the collusion and to eliminate competition."
"that is, people, instead of that of secret, now openly," said yesterday the Member péquiste Sylvain Simard at a press conference.
Earlier in the morning, Mr. Simard has raised the issue in the National Assembly because it said see how the public interest can be used in this way.
The Minister of Natural Resources, Nathalie Normandeau, replied in the afternoon, vigorously denied that there was collusion for this contract.
"I am beginning to have my trip," she complaining, claiming that the PQ had had been "dishonest" and had "lacked rigour."
She said that "it would be the least" that the PQ subsequently apologizes.
The consortia formula is a common practice in the world.
It is usually a time-limited alliance to two or more companies to combine their respective expertise in order to respond to a call for tenders for a complex project.
The project Eastmain contains a high level of complexity in view of the scale of the work.
The shipyard is underway and must continue until 2012.
However, the contract was awarded without competition to act; there were negotiations.
Also, the formula of consortia is no longer an exception in Quebec, even for relatively simple projects.
As the last week revealed Le Devoir, the formula of the consortia in the sector of the génie-conseil investigated in government.
A quick overview of the register of Quebec firms will count more than 200 consortia, some of which appear to be permanent.
Thus, the firm Dessau works in partnership with most of its main competitors, CIMA +, Génivar, PAE and other Tecsult and Roche.
Each combination, and there are dozens, down to one and the same legal person, Dessau.
As regards the consortium stewardship, the Energy Minister Normandeau stressed that "the territory of the James Bay responded to particular dynamics of workforce and Hydro-Québec is responding in particular since the 70 s."
The boss of the project Eastmain, Réal Laporte, of the James Bay Power Corporation (SEBJ), gave an explanation which was batting on the fact that the contract of stewardship of the project has been granted awards.
"if you're going to tender and that there is little of bidders, your price will be higher."
"you have two choices: either you take the people who are in this market and you say: we will negotiate a satisfactory agreement and with a good price."
"but the idea is that this is not the price which is important, it is the competence of the people," said Mr. Laporte.
This contract is awarded to the Energy consortium stewardship is part of a long list of contracts Parti Quebecois of more than $50 000.
The contracts were granted by Hydro-Quebec and SEBJ for the Eastmain- 1 project -A-Sarcelle-Rupert.
After verification, Le Devoir has arts-sector 109 génie-conseil contracts issued to between 2002 and March 2010 to companies or their subsidiaries, including laboratories of soil.
PAE has swept 22 contracts, Génivar had 16, Tecsult 14 and Dessau 10, its participation in Energy Stewardship.
All contracts have been negotiated.
They account for 449 783 $344, including the contract to Energy Stewardship $295 131 564.
Sylvain Simard has suggested that the four firms that make up the consortium (OPI, Dessau, SM Group and Axor) are "well known to the Quebec Liberal Party."
The Minister Normandeau that the PQ subsequently is also linked to these firms that finance ,"" before it was more of its leaders.
