Hackers vengeful and spies in
The WikiLeaks case has a double value.
On the one hand, it is an apparent scandal, a scandal that is as scandal in the hypocrisy which governs relations between the Member States, citizens and the press.
On the other, it promises profound changes at the international level, and suggests a future dominated by the regression.
But in order.
The first aspect of WikiLeaks, is the confirmation of the fact that each record by a secret service (of any nation) is composed exclusively of press clippings.
The "extraordinary" American revelations about the sexual habits of Berlusconi only report on what for months could be read in any newspaper (except those whose Berlusconi owns), and the eerily typical profile of Gaddafi was for a long time for the cabaret artists to SKIT.
The rule that the secret files must be that new compounds already known is essential to the dynamics of the secret services, and not only in this century.
If you go into a bookshop on esoteric publications, you will see that each book repeat (on the Holy Grail, the mystery of Rennes-le-Château, the Templiers or Rose-Croix) exactly what was written in the earlier books.
And not only because the author of dark texts do not make new research (or like knows where to look for new on the non-existent), but because those dedicated to occultism only believe that they know already, and that confirm what they had already learned.
It is the mechanism of the success of Dan Brown.
For secret files.
The informant is lazy, lazy (or limited spirit) and the head of the secret services (or it could be, whatever, editor of Libération), which is as true that what he acknowledges.
The top secret information on Berlusconi said that the US embassy in Rome sent to the State Department were the same as Newsweek published the week before.
So why the revelations on these matters have caused a great deal of noise?
On the one hand, they say that any person cultivated already knows, namely the embassies, at least since the end of the Second World War, and since the Heads of states can call or take a plane to meet for dinner, have lost their diplomatic service and, with the exception of a few years of representation, into centres of espionage.
Any spectator of films knows this very well, and it is only through hypocrisy pretending to ignore.
However, the fact of the repeat in public violates the duty of hypocrisy, and is in a bad light American diplomacy.
Secondly, the idea that a hacker would capture the most secret secrets of the most powerful country in the world is a significant blow to the prestige of the State Department.
As the scandal is not putting both in crisis victims as the "torturers."
But the very nature of what happened.
Orwell once, at the time, it could produce power as a Big Brother, which controlled every gesture of his subjects.
The Orwellian prophecy was completely proved since, that can monitor each movement through the telephone, the hotel visited each transaction, the motorway and so on, the citizen became the victim of the eye of the power.
But when it is shown, as it happens, that even the cryptes secrets of power to the control of a hacker, the report continues to be unidirectional and becomes circular.
The power control every citizen, but every citizen, or at least the hacker - elected as avenger of the citizen -, can know all the secrets of power.
How a power which no longer has the option of retaining its own secret take?
Georg Simmel already said, it is true that a secret true is a secret secret (vacuum and vacuum can never be revealed); it is true, too, that know everything about the nature of Berlusconi or Merkel is indeed a secret vacuum of secrecy, because in the public domain; but, as WikiLeaks has done, that the secrets of Hillary Clinton were empty secret means pull any power.
WikiLeaks has done no harm to Sarkozy and Merkel, but has done too much to Clinton and Obama.
The consequences of this wound to a very strong power?
It is clear that in the future, governments can no longer put online no reserved - that would be to publish information on a poster hung up on the street corner.
But it is equally obvious that with current technology, it is vain hope to maintain confidential reports by telephone.
Well, it's easy to find out if and when a head of state has shifted in aircraft and approached one of his colleagues.
How can be maintained in the future the private reports and reserved?
For the moment, I know that my anticipation notes of science fiction and is therefore romantic, but I am obliged to imagine government agents who move in a discreet manner in uncontrollable mail coach travel, carrying messages learned by heart or, at most, in hiding the rare written information in the Achilles a shoe.
The information will be kept in single copy in closed drawers to key: basically the espionage attempt of the Watergate has had less success than WikiLeaks.
I have had the opportunity to write that the technology is now in crab, i.e. backwards.
A century after the wireless telegraph revolutionised communications, the Internet has restored a telegraph on son (telephone).
The video (analogue) had allowed the researchers in film to explore a film step by step, moving forward and back and see all the secrets of the assembly, but now the CD (digital) do that to jump to chapter by chapter, i.e. by macroportions.
With high-speed trains, you go from Rome to Milan in three hours, while in flight, andparticipants that LLEX.com www.llrx.com, it takes three and a half hours.
It is therefore not extraordinary that the policy and communications techniques for cars.
A final observation.
In the past, the press was trying to understand what was going on in the secrecy of the embassies.
Now, are the embassies seeking confidential information to the press.
Climate: how France quick fix its promises of funding
A year after the Copenhagen Agreement, it is time to examine the promises of funding quickly released so-called fast start funding or (early) made by the developed countries.
And the French were tampering.
In the Copenhagen Accord, the developed countries are committed to provide $30 billion between 2010 and 2012.
The European Union has pledged EUR 7.2 billion over three years and France 1.26 billion euros (420 million per year).
At the opening of the COP16, the EU has lifted the great game to persuade its partners to the reality of its commitment to the fast start funding: report detailing the activities of its Member States, press conference, general side event, distribution of brochures...
The operation transparency is valuable and valued: developing countries and civil society would like all developed countries to do the same with the same level of precision.
The EU reached EUR 2010 2.2 billion, which puts on the right path for the respect of its commitment of $7.2 billion in 2012.
But when one looks at in detail, things are more complicated.
This money must be, according to the Copenhagen agreement, "new and additional," in order to ensure that an additional effort is carried out without being at the expense of official development assistance.
Unfortunately, there is no agreement on what "new and additional" means.
While the European Commission had proposed a harmonisation, some Member States, including France have blocked the procedure.
Today, everyone chooses the reference which best suits them.
The European Commission, for example, has seen as the reference year 2009: the international funding, and it adds 150 million over three years of fast start funding.
Other countries have chosen similar references in terms of the year or in terms of level of official development assistance.
By contrast, France believes that the funding of "all new projects" of the year 2010 are "new and additional."
In other words, there is no reference to previous years' expenditures or at the global level of official development assistance.
Specifically, the total amount of France's support to developing countries can remain stable (or decline), she claims to respect its commitment of funding "new and additional..."
Another crucial element, the division between donations and loans.
Again, there is no rule and everyone chooses its method of calculation.
Some, such as France, consider that €1 paid equivalent to €1.
Of course, it is hard to justify: this is not comparable.
If the use of loans can be justified for certain investments that are profitable (often projects related to the reduction of emissions that are based on more efficient technologies), it is misleading to present an euro will recover as equivalent to an euro given... Everything, should be arts-sector under its commitments that the cost of the loan to the lender countries (the equivalent of an interest rate).
But France has a line of reasoning: it "respects" its commitment of EUR 420 million in 91.5% of loans (389.8 million) and 8.5% of donations (36.1 million euros) - see the document the EU to check for yourself.
It is the only country of the Union to use if the loan on a massive scale.
Germany requires 46%, while Denmark, the Netherlands and Slovakia (other) are meeting their commitments with 100% of donations.
In other words, when the vast majority of the European Union is €1 to meet its commitment, France is only 10 cents, and considers that the effort is comparable.
A sleight of hand!
In summary, in his fast start funding, France operates a double scam: on the one hand on the evolution of the action in the time and the other on the reality of the financial effort.
While spending that EUR 36.1 million, she comes to believe that she spends 420 million "new and additional" consistent with its promises.
The manipulation of the Department of Finance (because, it seems that it is Bercy who has achieved the arbitration) could have a double negative impact, both within the EU (why the other Member States would continue to give it enough to pay?) and in the negotiations since developing countries are not completely fooled...
The early funding is only a small matter, on the short term, in the context of discussions on the climate.
But it could be a grain of sand in the huge machine that is the UNFCCC.
Let us hope that this will not be the case.
However, it is essential to learn the lessons of this first year of early funding.
Firstly, France could announce a change in the way of accounting for the years 2011 and 2012, in a spirit of respect of its commitments and equity with the other countries of the European Union.
But above all, France could move the discussions on the issues of long-term funding (another crucial chapter currently being discussed): we will be forced to take the issue of "additionality" or the method of calculating loans.
France could change its position to become progressive on these issues it is - on others.
The hope is based on the new Minister of the Environment, Mrs Kosciusko-Morizet, who will arrive in Cancun next week.
A surprise announcement on the fast start of France and on his vision of "additionality" and the use of loans would increase the level of international confidence necessary for progress in the discussions.
Warning to pesticides ingested by children
A 10 -year-old interfering in a day 81 different chemicals, according to a study published on Wednesday of the WBWA Générations Future (ex- Movement for Rights and respect of future generations).
The association, which warns that its results "have no significant statistical value given the low number of samples analyzed, but are to include the issues dealt with," generally purchased between July and September the food consumed in four meals and a snack in one day by a child of a decade, Oise in supermarkets and Paris.
These meals types, including the official recommendations - five fresh fruit and vegetables, three dairy products and 1.5 litre of water a day - as well as sweets, were examined by laboratories in search of chemicals, pesticides, heavy metals and other pollutants.
The base is damning: 81 chemicals, 42 of which are classified as carcinogenic possible or probable and five substances that are carcinogenic some 37 substances that act as endocrine disruptors (EP), according to studies by several institutions such as the International Centre for Research on Cancer.
"even if, in almost all cases, the legal limits for each individual chemical are not exceeded in our investigation, we can clearly see that the reality of consumer exposure to contaminants possibly carcinogenic and / or EP is worrying," notes the association.
For breakfast, butter and milk tea alone contain more than a decade of possible carcinogenic residues and three proved as carcinogenic some as well as almost a dozen residues likely to disrupt the hormonal system.
The potato, imported from Brazil, planned as a snack by the study, this traces of six chemicals, including a fungicide banned in France.
Same thing for green beans from Kenya, included in lunch, on which the study has detected traces of a powerful insecticide banned in the EU.
In addition, the minced meat, canned tuna, and even the wand of bread and the chewing gum were full of pesticides and other chemicals.
In the analyses have revealed the presence of nitrates and chloroform.
For the dinner, the salmon steak was the most "rich" with 34 chemical residues detected and even the consideration of the plastic base used to warm the micro-onde was not free meals.
The final risk for the consumer to this "cocktails of contaminants" "is probably underestimated," according to the study.
The Alliance Europe Ecologie-Les Greens (EE-LV), for its part, has proposed "faced with the urgency of the situation" for a moratorium on the use of pesticides, in order to stop "the increase in diseases of civilisation."
In July, a study of the European Food Safety Authority (EFSA) the presence of 365 different pesticides identified residues in fruit and vegetables consumed in Europe, including 76 in cereals.
